The paper deals with multi-user detection in a spread spectrum system, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The use of belief propagation as a detection algorithm also falls under the category of statistical inference (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper presents a new derivation of the minimum mean square error formula, which is a topic in linear algebra and optimization (cs.LG).
